Tourists arrivals to Cyprus in April
rose 43 percent from a year earlier to 199,762, mainly on a
rebound in arrivals from the U.K., the governmentâ€™s  Statistical
Service  said.  British tourists visiting Cyprus last month rose 29 percent
to 80,998, the service said in a  statement  on its website today.
January to April arrivals rose 18 percent to 405,463, mainly on
a 61 percent increase in Russian visitors.  Tourism accounts directly and indirectly for about one
